The article is a statement issued on June 1, 2020, regarding the celebration of Global Coptic Day. It sends best wishes to Coptic Christians around the world and recognizes their contributions, legacy, and ongoing challenges. The statement also emphasizes the role of faith, prayer, and service, especially during the COVID-19 pandemic. It calls for God's healing and comfort for those affected by the virus. Additionally, it highlights the importance of religious freedom and the need to promote and defend it globally. The article mentions previous efforts to address religious persecution and discrimination and calls for continued action to ensure everyone can worship freely and without fear. The statement concludes by expressing hopes for a joyful and purposeful celebration.